Policy.acknowledgement_statement:
Funding support for the Genomic Origins and Admixture in Latinos (GOAL) Study was provided by the National Institute of General Medical Sciences (1R01GM090087). Additional support for sample collection was provided by a grant from the Stanley J. Glaser Foundation and the Dr. John T. Macdonald Foundation Department of Human Genetics. The datasets used for the analyses described in this manuscript were obtained from dbGaP through dbGaP accession number phs000750.v1.p1.
We request that publications resulting from these data cite the original publication: Moreno-Estrada A, Williams S, Gravel S, Zakharia F, McCauley JL, Byrnes JK, Gignoux CR, Ortiz-Tello P, Martinez RJ, Hedges DJ, Morris RW, Eng C, Sandoval K, Acevedo S, Martinez-Cruzado JC, Norman PJ, Layrisse Z, Parham P, Gonzalez-Burchard E, Cuccaro ML, Martin ER, Bustamante CD. Reconstructing the Population Genetic History of the Caribbean. PLOS Genet, 2013 Nov; 9(11):e1003925. doi: 10.1371/journal.pgen.1003925. Epub 2013 Nov 14. PMCID: PMC3828151.
